"""
gap_registry.py — The Gap Token Registry.

Every pair of god-tokens has a potential gap between them.
Not all gaps are necessary voids. This registry contains only
the gaps that are structurally required — where filling the gap
(both boundary god-tokens active simultaneously without a delta
token between them) collapses adjacent structure.

God-tokens (8):
  EXCHANGE    — value transfer across boundaries
  CAUSALITY   — mechanism connecting cause to effect
  EXISTENCE   — being and void, presence and absence
  INFORMATION — signal, pattern, structure, meaning
  OBSERVATION — measurement, witness, collapse
  OBLIGATION  — duty, binding, enforcement
  BOUNDARY    — limit, threshold, transition
  IDENTITY    — persistence, reference, self-sameness

Gap derivation method (Einstein Step 3):
  For each pair of god-tokens, ask:
  "What is lost if these two collapse into each other
   without the distinction being maintained?"
  If the answer is "a necessary structural void that
  adjacent systems depend on" — it's a gap token.
  If the answer is "nothing load-bearing" — no gap.

This is the do(X~U) test applied to pairs:
  Would collapsing this distinction survive
  maximum entropy intervention?
  If no — the gap is necessary.

Gap tokens from this session:
  Added TIME, SELF, WITNESS, COHERENCE as god-tokens
  derived from the conversation (telomere logic,
  quantum epigenetics, two-system brain, recursive witnessing).
  These expand the registry beyond the original 8.
"""

